news.title: PropShare raises Rs 367 crore from WestBridge Capital & Pravega Ventures
news.para: "By partnering with WestBridge Capital, we plan to grow to over $1 billion in transacted assets on the platform by expanding into newer geographies and property types, while keeping technology and our investors at the core of our offering," said Hashim Khan, CTO, Propshare.

news.title: Now, Chandigarh administration officials to visit Delhi to meet MHA officials
news.para: The UT administration had last converted leasehold plots into freehold in 1983 in commercial category. The matter was also taken by up MP Kirron Kher with the MHA and ministry of urban development (MoUD).

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CRDA to lease out flats built for government employees
news.para: In the first lot, the CRDA has put up the D1 Tower, containing 120 flats, for lease to earn about Rs 8-10 crore per annum.
